  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile, COU omitted)",
  "description": "This unit of assurance documents credibility evidence for a CFD hemolysis prediction model of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump. The model has been applied in clinical research settings to support ventricular assist device design decisions and regulatory submissions. A Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification campaign was executed across operating flow rates of 3–7 L/min and rotational speeds of 2500–5500 RPM. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors were evaluated; seven were formally assessed and six were scoped out due to epistemic limitations at the applicable model risk level. Despite these gaps, aggregate evidence was judged sufficient under the Minimal profile for the intended engineering decision. Note: structured Context of Use metadata is not encoded in this package; the intended-use scope is conveyed only through this narrative description.",
